TransUnion Namibia country manager Lara Burger says this mitigates the effects of a global economic slowdown and ensures sustainable and inclusive economic growth. The company's Head of commercial bureau solutions Rafi Kotler says data-based tools are proving to be a key driver of the growing trend of SMEs expanding beyond Namibia's borders into the region and globally. “Big data and analytics used to be seen as something only large enterprises could afford, or use. That's changing rapidly, with Namibia's SMEs increasingly turning to data-driven business intelligence tools to grow their businesses, access new markets and develop their pipelines,” he says. --The Namibian--